Mentree

DESIGN PROJECT

An internal social media site for companies to match their employees up as mentors and mentees based on their personalities and skills. Including features such as chatting, making calendar events, taking polls, reading articles, and more.

My Role

Initially I started developing the functionality using Django, but as another developer was on-boarded I moved to solely working on the designs. I created a complete mockup using AdobeXD and implemented using HTML/CSS/JS.

Project Difficulties

Since the company was so small I had to do all sorts of different tasks, from researching users, collecting user data, designing on my own, and performing user testing. It was a lot of tasks to manage in such a short period of time.

My Solution

I planned out all of the tasks that needed to be done and started delegating the non-technical tasks to the rest of the team. Then I took a gamified approach to design the application. I made the UI very fun and colorful to entice employees to use it often. Making it feel less like a web application and more like a game, without compromising the usability.

Notable Contributions
  • Redesigned existing logo
  • Created new color scheme for application
  • Created user research surveys and testing procedure

Quincy Green

DESIGN PROJECT

A cannabis farm in need of a website redesign from 4 years ago. They went through a rebranding but their website didn’t match the way they wanted to represent their brand.

My Role

I worked in a team of five designers to create a full case study on the current website and identify pieces that need to be changed.

Project Difficulties

The client knew vaguely what he wanted but wasn’t very clear with the requirements. This was one of my first case studies so I did a lot of research and reading to make sure I was doing everything effectively and efficiently.

My Solution

Parts of the old site were unusable and not mobile friendly, so we created an improved mockup on AdobeXD for the web application.

Notable Contributions
  • Conducted user research and research on competitor farms
  • Created personas of potential users of the site
  • Designed entire web application in AdobeXD and conducted user testing using prototype, old website, and competitors
  • Increased user satisfaction from 20% to 95% with prototype

Happy News

REACT PROJECT

A personal project I undertook to help create a more positive experience for people during the pandemic. All news has become centered around it and I didn’t like that there were no positive articles being shown in mainstream media.

My Role

Develop this web application and make it user friendly and mobile friendly. Improve the mood of the public.

Project Difficulties

I don’t have much experience working with APIs so finding out how to connect the responses to my HTML elements was tricky at first.

My Solution

I created a simple frontend and limited functionality so that I could return results more easily. Though in the future I would like a functioning search bar, my current implementation meets my requirements and is presented well.

Typing Game

JAVASCRIPT PROJECT

A personal project I made after I got obsessed with typeracer to practice my javascript skills. The game generates random quotes using a random quote API and counts your score based on how many quotes you type out.

My Role

Develop this web application and make it more aesthetically pleasing than type-racer’s UI.

Project Difficulties

I don’t have much experience working with APIs so connecting the responses to my HTML elements was tricky. Another difficulty was implementing all the functionality like the timer, and score variables, but I quickly figured it out.

My Solution

I created a simple frontend and limited functionality so that I could return results easily. Use large block text to make the UI focused on the type as it would be appropriate for a typing game.
